> What if I replaced my heat control boxes with smooth straight pipes and controlled my heat as close to my dash as possible with one giant heat control box????

You'd melt down the HE's. They're designed to have air flowing through
them whenever the engine's running. The control boxes just control
where it goes. Either to the cabin or dumped outside.

